From: ETK GTK Edition <mercurious>
Subject: [PATCH v0.7.5] simplify crash-overlay text to "GTK Crash Recovery"

Release-prep polish (v0.7.1 kit release dossier, 2026-07-22): all three
anti-lock rescue notices now show the same mixed-case "GTK Crash Recovery"
-- the all-caps radio-speak variants were less legible on the rig panel
(operator-directed). Durations unchanged (8 s recovering / 5 s absorbed).
Version self-id bumped to v0.7.5 (get_verbose_version -> --version, log
header, about dialog).

Incremental over etk-rpcs3-gtk-edition-0.7.4-dev-ffs-v5-avwiden-v1.patch.
Artifact: rpcs3-etk_gtk-edition-0.7.5_v0.0.41-19544-60c9705a_linux_aarch64.AppImage
sha256 c464771932da20064f0942fc61f22df9d6e67bc52893f319d5d02cde1eaae02d
(packaged via scripts/package-appimage.sh, MARKER="GTK Crash Recovery",
VERIFY OK with system ffmpeg hidden).
---
--- a/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/VK/vkutils/sync.cpp
+++ b/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/VK/vkutils/sync.cpp
@@ -650,7 +650,7 @@
 		}
 		if (now - since >= ETK_STALL_WARN_US && !pfence->etk_stale_warned.exchange(true))
 		{
-			etk_queue_rescue_notice("GTK RESCUE: RECOVERING FROM CRASH - STANDBY, KEEP AT THE CONTROLS", 8'000'000);
+			etk_queue_rescue_notice("GTK Crash Recovery", 8'000'000);
 		}
 		if (now - since < etk_fence_force_threshold_us())
